text.tspan: Prevalence of Polio Rates in the United States, 1910-2010
The reported rates are per 100,000 US population and include both wild- and vaccine-derived type polio infections
that occurred indigenously and as imported cases.
Source: Our World In Data based on US Public Health Service (1910-1951) and US Center for Disease Control (1960-2010)
